### Semantic Tags

**The important ones:**

<header> – Defines the top section of a page or section, usually containing titles, logos, or navigation.

<nav> – Represents a navigation area that contains links to other sections or pages.

<main> – Contains the main content of the webpage; only one <main> should be used per page.

<section> – Groups related content into a logical section or topic of a webpage.

<article> – Represents independent, self-contained content such as a blog post or news article.

<aside> – Holds content indirectly related to the main content, like sidebars or additional notes.

<footer> – Defines the bottom part of a page or section, usually including copyright or contact info.

<figure> – Wraps visual media like images or charts along with their captions.

<figcaption> – Provides a caption or description for the content inside a <figure>.

<time> – Represents dates or times in a machine-readable format.
